<div class="form-container">
<div class="text-container">
<h2>What is MISSQL Command?</h2>
<p>MISSQL command is a web application designed to help you learn SQL, the language of <del>love</del> databases.</p>
<p>Sign up to become a MISSQL commander, and you'll work your way through ten levels that teach and test your SQL knowledge while you save the world from nuclear annihilation.</p><p>You'll learn everything from how to get data out of a database, to how to create and drop tables and and perform complex operations like JOINS.</p>
<p>No idea what any of that means? Then MISSQL command is definitely for you.</p>
</div>
<%= form_for @user, :html => {:class => 'form sign-up-form'} do |f|%>
<h2>Sign Up</h2>
<fieldset>
	<%= f.label :email, "Email Address*:" %>
 	<%= f.text_field :email %>
</fieldset>
<fieldset>
	<%= f.label :user_name, "Username:" %> 
	<%= f.text_field :user_name %> 
</fieldset>
<fieldset>
	<%= f.label :password, "Password:" %> 
	<%= f.password_field :password %> 
</fieldset>
<fieldset>
	<%= f.label :password_confirmation, "Confirm password:" %> 
	<%= f.password_field :password_confirmation %>  
</fieldset>
<fieldset>
	<%= f.submit %>
</fieldset>
<% end %>
</div>